DJs Infamous Coconut Banana Pancakes Recipe
Ingredients
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
	‚ÅÉ	2 c All Purpose Flour
	‚ÅÉ	3 tsp Baking Powder
	‚ÅÉ	3 tbsp Cane Sugar
	‚ÅÉ	1/2 tsp Sea Salt
	‚ÅÉ	10 tbsp Unsweetened Shredded Coconut 
	‚ÅÉ	2 Bananas, medium-sized, small dice
	‚ÅÉ	2 Eggs
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Water
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Milk
	‚ÅÉ	3/4 c Whole Milk
	‚ÅÉ	1 tsp Vanilla Extract
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Coconut Oil, melted
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Unsalted Butter, melted (+ more to butter griddle)
	‚ÅÉ	Extra Virgin Olive Oil Spray, for griddle

Directions 
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
STEP 1: Mise en place & mix
	‚ÅÉ	Sift flour and baking soda into a large bowl.
	‚ÅÉ	Add sugar, salt and shredded coconut. Mix lightly with a wooden spoon.
	‚ÅÉ	In a separate bowl, lightly whisk eggs, coconut water, coconut milk, whole milk, vanilla extract, coconut oil and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Make a well in the center of flour mixture and pour in milk mixture.
	‚ÅÉ	Mix lightly to combine, leaving batter clumpy.
	‚ÅÉ	Add bananas to batter, briefly stir to distribute evenly.
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT overmix, a few lumps are ok.

STEP 2: Get to cooking
	‚ÅÉ	Heat lightly oiled griddle to 275 degrees or frying pan on medium, using a combination of spray and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Ladle or pour batter onto griddle, using 1 cup sized ladle or measuring cup for large cakes, 1/4 cup for small.
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until top of pancakes have bubbles and a few bursts, 2 - 3 minutes. Flip carefully with a thin spatula. 
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until brown and crisp, about 2 - 3 minutes, adding more spray and butter if needed.

STEP 3: Let‚Äôs eat!
	‚ÅÉ	Transfer to plate or platter and serve. 

Yield: 6 large Coconut Banana Pancakes

	‚Ä¢	Best w/100% maple syrup. 
	‚Ä¢	Use organic ingredients, if accessible. 

Enjoy!

üòàü•ûü•• üçå 

Great to see all your videos and AWESOME to see all the ways you guys are tweaking the recipe! 

Here‚Äôs the original recipe below from @chefputtieüë©üèæ‚Äçüç≥ 

Get down with these this weekend!!! 

DJ‚Äôs Infamous Coconut Banana Pancakes Recipe created by: CHEF PUTTIEüë©üèæ‚Äçüç≥
Ingredients
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
	‚ÅÉ	2 c All Purpose Flour
	‚ÅÉ	3 tsp Baking Powder
	‚ÅÉ	3 tbsp Cane Sugar
	‚ÅÉ	1/2 tsp Sea Salt
	‚ÅÉ	10 tbsp Unsweetened Shredded Coconut 
	‚ÅÉ	2 Bananas, medium-sized, small dice
	‚ÅÉ	2 Eggs
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Water
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Milk
	‚ÅÉ	3/4 c Whole Milk
	‚ÅÉ	1 tsp Vanilla Extract
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Coconut Oil, melted
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Unsalted Butter, melted (+ more to butter griddle)
	‚ÅÉ	Extra Virgin Olive Oil Spray, for griddle

Directions 
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
STEP 1: Mise en place & mix
	‚ÅÉ	Sift flour and baking powder into a large bowl.
	‚ÅÉ	Add sugar, salt and shredded coconut. Mix lightly with a wooden spoon.
	‚ÅÉ	In a separate bowl, lightly whisk eggs, coconut water, coconut milk, whole milk, vanilla extract, coconut oil and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Make a well in the center of flour mixture and pour in milk mixture.
	‚ÅÉ	Mix lightly to combine, leaving batter clumpy.
	‚ÅÉ	Add bananas to batter, briefly stir to distribute evenly.
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT overmix, a few lumps are ok.

STEP 2: Get to cooking
	‚ÅÉ	Heat lightly oiled griddle to 275 degrees or frying pan on medium, using a combination of spray and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Ladle or pour batter onto griddle, using 1 cup sized ladle or measuring cup for large cakes, 1/4 cup for small.
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until top of pancakes have bubbles and a few bursts, 2 - 3 minutes. Flip carefully with a thin spatula. 
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until brown and crisp, about 2 - 3 minutes, adding more spray and butter if needed.

STEP 3: Let‚Äôs eat!
	‚ÅÉ	Transfer to plate or platter and serve. 

Yield: 6 large Coconut Banana Pancakes

	‚Ä¢	Best w/100% maple syrup. 
	‚Ä¢	Use organic ingredients, if accessible. 
* and if you‚Äôre like DJ, smother the cakes in peanut butter üòäüí™üèæ

Eat wisely, Live fabulously ‚ù§Ô∏è

* SCROLL LEFT and I‚Äôll give you some context to some very cool history. 
25 years again TODAY, I had my first ever pro wrestling match in 1996 in front of 15,000 people in Corpus Christi, Texas for @WWE. 

Not only had I never wrestled an actual real match before, but I had NEVER wrestled in front of people. 

And I was so broke, the only thing I could afford to buy was a pair of white volleyball knee pads ü§£ü§¶üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
I called my uncle, ‚ÄúKing Haku‚Äù (pictured with Andre the Giant) and asked if I could borrow a pair of his wrestling trunks (he loved purple) and I borrowed a pair of my dads old wrestling boots that his tag team partner, George Wells used to wear (pictured in the ring). 

I remember before the match not being nervous at all - I could feel my adrenaline pump hard, but I was eerily calm. 

Told myself over and over, just go out there and be sharp and confident with your moves and block out the noise. 

That was a good strategy because the very first thing I heard when I walked thru the curtain as my name was announced to the arena, ‚ÄúDwaaaaaayne Johnsoooon‚Äù was 

‚ÄúYOU FUCKING SUCK‚Äù from a drunk fan üòÇüòÇüòÇ True story üëçüèæ

Man I look at this picture in complete awe and gratitude for the wild, unpredictable journey and at times - the tough roads this hard working, fanny pack wearing kid would go down.

 And for the record, the man I‚Äôm wrestling is the legendary Brooklyn Brawler. He was gracious enough to let me win my first ever match. 

Which is why it was important to me to lost my very last match. 

May sound strange, but that‚Äôs how you give back to the wrestling business when you leave it. 
You lose. 

And you move on down the road. 

#firstmatch‚òùüèæ
#peopleschamp ‚úäüèæ
#horriblehaircut üòÇ

The CFL changed my life. 

When you have nothing and you‚Äôre scratching and clawing for everything you can get - all in the spirit of making your football dreams come true. 

You become the hardest worker in the room. 

You will not be denied. 

I knew in my heart I was going to make it in the CFL - and parlay that into a very successful career in the NFL.
Maybe even win a Super Bowl...

But neither of those dreams came close to coming true. 

Truth is, I just wasn‚Äôt good enough and it wasn‚Äôt my time. 

The CFL sent me home. 
I was still grateful to a man who would eventually become a mentor and friend, Wally Buono for even giving me the opportunity. 
I had $7 bucks. 

But it‚Äôs funny how sometimes life comes full circle. 

Now I‚Äôm back.
Same hungry kid, but much different man. 

As an owner of the XFL, our discussions with the CFL have been very exciting. There‚Äôs a real pulse here because you can feel the unique opportunity we can potentially create together. 

Wherever it all leads, I can tell you this one is personal to me and is driven by all my passion - because me being cut by the CFL was the greatest thing that happened.
It set me on a path that years later would lead me right back to the league. 

To help create even greater and bigger opportunities for all our players and all our fans. 

As an owner who‚Äôs had his hands in the dirt - my loyalty will always lie with the players and fans. 

I‚Äôll keep you posted as our XFL/CFL discussions unfold. 
Got your back. 

So yes, the CFL changed my life, in ways I could‚Äôve never imagined üôèüèæ üá®üá¶ üèà

ENJOY and please let us know how your pancakes came out and more importantly, how you liked them! üëäüèæ

DJ‚Äôs Infamous Coconut Banana Pancakes Recipe created by: CHEF PUTTIEüë©üèæ‚Äçüç≥
Ingredients
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
	‚ÅÉ	2 c All Purpose Flour
	‚ÅÉ	3 tsp Baking Powder
	‚ÅÉ	3 tbsp Cane Sugar
	‚ÅÉ	1/2 tsp Sea Salt
	‚ÅÉ	10 tbsp Unsweetened Shredded Coconut 
	‚ÅÉ	2 Bananas, medium-sized, small dice
	‚ÅÉ	2 Eggs
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Water
	‚ÅÉ	1 c Coconut Milk
	‚ÅÉ	3/4 c Whole Milk
	‚ÅÉ	1 tsp Vanilla Extract
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Coconut Oil, melted
	‚ÅÉ	2 tbsp Unsalted Butter, melted (+ more to butter griddle)
	‚ÅÉ	Extra Virgin Olive Oil Spray, for griddle

Directions 
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
STEP 1: Mise en place & mix
	‚ÅÉ	Sift flour and baking powder into a large bowl.
	‚ÅÉ	Add sugar, salt and shredded coconut. Mix lightly with a wooden spoon.
	‚ÅÉ	In a separate bowl, lightly whisk eggs, coconut water, coconut milk, whole milk, vanilla extract, coconut oil and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Make a well in the center of flour mixture and pour in milk mixture.
	‚ÅÉ	Mix lightly to combine, leaving batter clumpy.
	‚ÅÉ	Add bananas to batter, briefly stir to distribute evenly.
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT overmix, a few lumps are ok.

STEP 2: Get to cooking
	‚ÅÉ	Heat lightly oiled griddle to 275 degrees or frying pan on medium, using a combination of spray and butter.
	‚ÅÉ	Ladle or pour batter onto griddle, using 1 cup sized ladle or measuring cup for large cakes, 1/4 cup for small.
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until top of pancakes have bubbles and a few bursts, 2 - 3 minutes. Flip carefully with a thin spatula. 
	‚ÅÉ	Cook until brown and crisp, about 2 - 3 minutes, adding more spray and butter if needed.

STEP 3: Let‚Äôs eat!
	‚ÅÉ	Transfer to plate or platter and serve. 

Yield: 6 large Coconut Banana Pancakes

	‚Ä¢	Best w/100% maple syrup. 
	‚Ä¢	Use organic ingredients, if accessible. 
* and if you‚Äôre like DJ, smother the cakes in peanut butter üòäüí™üèæ

Eat wisely, Live fabulously ‚ù§Ô∏è

~ Chef Puttie üë©üèæ‚Äçüç≥
